# App Style Guide Rules

When writing or editing React components in `components/` or `app/`, always follow the project style guide at `documentation/style_guide.md`. Prefer the reusable CSS classes in `app/globals.css` over inline Tailwind when they match.

## Reusable CSS Classes (prefer these)

- **Layout**: `sticky-header`, `header-bar`, `app-view`, `sheet-header`, `sheet-body`, `sheet-footer`
- **Typography**: `heading-section`, `heading-dialog`, `body-large`, `label-form`, `text-muted-sm`, `text-muted-xs`
- **Surfaces**: `card-surface`, `content-box`, `surface-muted`, `state-active`

## Typography

- **Page/section/card heading**: use `heading-section`
- **Dialog/sheet title**: `text-xl font-bold` — this is the ONLY place `font-bold` is used for headings
- **Body text**: `text-sm`
- **Body large**: use `body-large`
- **Muted text (sm)**: use `text-muted-sm`
- **Muted text (xs)**: use `text-muted-xs`
- **Form label**: use `label-form`
- Never use `text-2xl` for card or dialog titles
- Prefer `font-semibold` over `font-bold` for in-page headings

## Cards and Surfaces

- **Standard card**: Use the `Card` component from `components/ui/card`
- **Inline card** (where Card component doesn't fit): use `card-surface`
- **Content box**: use `content-box`
- **Muted surface**: use `surface-muted`
- **Active state**: use `state-active`
- Always use `rounded-xl` for cards and bordered containers. Never use `rounded-2xl` for cards.
- Use `rounded-lg` only for muted surfaces and skeleton placeholders.

## Page Layout

- **View wrapper**: use `app-view`
- Views must NOT add their own `px-*` or `py-*` — the parent layout provides `container mx-auto px-4`
- Use `space-y-6` between major sections, `space-y-2` within sections

## Sheet/Dialog Headers

- **Sheet header**: use `sheet-header`
- **Sheet body**: use `sheet-body`
- **Sheet footer**: use `sheet-footer`
- **Sheet title**: use `heading-section`

## Icons

- **Standard**: `h-4 w-4`
- **Large**: `h-5 w-5`
- **Small**: `h-3.5 w-3.5`
- Always use `h-X w-X` syntax. Never use `size-X`.

## Semantic Colors

- **Success**: use `text-success` — never use `text-green-500` or `text-green-600` directly
- **Warning/hide**: use `text-warning` — never use `text-orange-600` directly
- **Active accent**: `text-primary`
- **Destructive**: `text-destructive`
- **Muted**: `text-muted-foreground`
- Use theme tokens over raw color values whenever a semantic match exists
